sentences: Isaiah "Rashad" Joel McClain (born May 16, 1991) is an American rapper.
His first big break was performing on the 2012 Smoker's Club Tour with rappers Juicy J, Joey Badass and Smoke DZA among others.
In March 2013, Rashad signed to the Carson, California-based record label Top Dawg Entertainment.
On January 28, 2014, he released Cilvia Demo, his first extended play, via digital distribution.
Off the buzz from the release of the EP, Rashad was named to the 2014 XXL freshman class.
On September 2, 2016, he released his debut studio album, The Sun's Tirade, to further acclaim.
On July 30, 2021, he released his long-awaited second album, The House Is Burning.
Isaiah Joel McClain was born on May 16, 1991, in Chattanooga, Tennessee.
